Biography

CLUB: Competed for Sunshine Volleyball Club for 10 years … Finished 3rd at Junior Nationals in 2016, 2018 and 2019 … Been in the national Top-5 since 2015 and finished #1 in Southern California in 2019.

HIGH SCHOOL: Graduated from Marymount High School in Los Angeles, Calif. in 2021 … Earned a distinction in photography … Lettered two years as a setter under Head Coach Carl Klein at MHS in the Mission League … In her junior season, played in 82 sets and garnered 214 assists, 16 aces and 63 digs … As a junior, was named MVP of the team and served as team captain … Helped MHS to Mission League Championship titles all three years … Finished as a State semifinalist and ranked 5th nationally in 2018 … Finished with a #10 national ranking in 2019 … Helped team to Nike Tournament of Champions and Dave Mohs Tournament crowns in 2019 … Also lettered in beach volleyball.

PERSONAL: Majoring in Psychology at Pepperdine and has career aspirations of being a therapist and mental health specialist … Daughter of Denise and Ken Kilroy … Has five siblings: Bridget, Megan, Ross, Kevin and Nora … Sister Kevin attends the Pepperdine Law School … In 2019, she was nominated to be in the Leukemia and Lymphoma Society Student of the Year campaign, serving in honor of her middle school principal who died of leukemia and raising over $70,000 in the seven-week campaign … Stated this as why she chose Pepperdine: “I chose to attend Pepperdine because of how welcoming and supportive the community is. Not only is the school amazing, but the coaches and team are already like family. They make sure everyone feels welcomed and appreciated which is not something you get everywhere.”

FAVORITES: Mookie Betts (pro athlete) … LA Dodgers (pro team) … The Fault in Our Stars by John Green (book) … Remember the Titans (movie) … Grey’s Anatomy (TV show) … Taylor Swift (musical artist) … sushi and boba (food) … baseball (sport other than volleyball) … hiking with her dog, trying new foods, traveling and photography (hobbies and pastimes).
